HEADWORD: Hemialbumose
<hw>Hem`i*al"bu"mose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hemi-</ets> + <ets>albumose</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>An albuminous substance formed in gastric digestion,
and by the action of boiling dilute acids on albumin. It is readily
convertible into hemipeptone. Called also
<altname>hemialbumin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemianaesthesia</ent>⟦br⟧
